I think monster summoning 3 should summon real NPCs. I don't see how a mob that is doubling for 120 with 65% haste is going to outdamag a pet quading for 77 wearing muzzle and 65% haste. Also epic pets have regen like water pets and a damage shield and procs. A summoned NPC will have none of this making it's use very limited but useful all the same in certain circumstances. The mages that complain that if anything might dare be somewhat as good as a epic pet need to get over themselves.  I see pets out damaging normal experience mobs all the time. Epic pets can solo golems in the grey and I saw a epic pet take a shimmering rockfiend to 40% health before dying and that was pre-upgrade.<br>
<br>
So please shut-up about epic pets. They kick ass and with the upgraded epic parsing 85 to 90dps on normal experience mobs you have little to fear and that isn't even including the damage shield.<br>
